body:
Fix UVM tests/20sequences/07start_item_seq and others which have code that is currently mis-executing after a $finish statement has executed earlier.

Short of treating everything like a process disable, which has performance concerns, or using exceptions which "just no", my plan is to add a finish check after every function call that might call $finish (determined recursively).  @gezalore for awareness in case hits what you are working on or otherwise have ideas.

For speed reasons I don't expect to treat stop similarly, since stops are more common and usually on assertion paths which will never execute.

<details>
<summary>Example</summary>
```
module t;

  class job;
    virtual function void check();
      $display("%m");
    endfunction
  endclass

  job j;
  bit did_finish;
  bit did_more;

  class cls;
    job q[$];
    virtual function void push();
      job newj;
      newj = new;
      q.push_back(newj);
    endfunction
    virtual function void work();
      if (0 == q.size()) begin
        did_finish = 1;
        $finish;
      end
      did_more = 1;
      j = q.pop_front();
      j.check();
    endfunction
  endclass

  initial begin
    cls c;
    c = new;
    c.push();
    c.push();
    c.work();
    j.check();
    c.work();
    j.check();

    c.work();  // Should $finish
    j.check();  // Should not be called
    $display("** UVM TEST FAILED **");
  end

  final begin
    if (!did_finish) $stop;
    else if (did_more) $stop;
    else $display("-*- All Finished -*-");
  end

endmodule
```
</details>

